We design Flint to be portable.


== RHEL/CentOS 6.7

The default g++ package is too old to build Flint.
A workaround for the issue is using devtoolset-3's g++.
Based on the instructions in
<https://www.softwarecollections.org/en/scls/rhscl/devtoolset-3/>,
you can install it as follows:
$ sudo yum install scl-utils
(download the package rhscl-devtoolset-3-*.noarch.rpm)
$ sudo yum install rhscl-devtoolset-3-*.noarch.rpm
$ sudo yum install devtoolset-3-gcc-c++
$ scl enable devtoolset-3 bash


== RHEL/CentOS 7

Install necessary tools for building and installing Flint with:
$ sudo yum install gcc gcc-c++ autoconf automake libtool cmake java-1.7.0-openjdk \
    wget zlib-devel


== Debian jessie/stretch/sid

We do not have a Debian package (.deb) for Flint yet.
Before building Flint, you will want to install prerequisite Debian packages
as follows:
$ sudo apt-get install gcc g++ autoconf automake libtool cmake openjdk-7-jdk \
    pkgconf zlib1g-dev


== Fedora 23

Use dnf(8) to install required packages for building Flint:
$ sudo dnf install gcc gcc-c++ autoconf automake libtool cmake java-1.8.0-openjdk \
    wget zlib-devel


== Ubuntu 16.04 LTS (Xenial Xerus)

$ sudo apt install g++ autoconf automake libtool cmake openjdk-8-jdk zlib1g-dev


== Ubuntu 14.04.3 LTS (Trusty Tahr)

All you have to do for installing necessary tools is:
$ sudo apt-get install g++ autoconf automake libtool cmake openjdk-7-jdk


